-- German Poultry Production Climbed 2.5% in 2011, Ministry Says
-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 2012-03-27T16:39:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/german-poultry-production-climbed-2-5-in-2011-ministry-says.html
German poultry production rose 2.5
percent to 1.66 million metric tons last year, the Food &
Agriculture Ministry reported.  Output included 1.19 million tons of chicken, 401,000 tons
of turkey meat, 63,000 tons of duck and 4,500 tons of goose, the
ministry said in a  statement  on its website today.  Imports of poultry rose 26 percent to 98,300 tons and
exports increased 5.4 percent to 312,700 tons, the statement
showed. National per-capita poultry consumption rose 0.2
kilogram (0.4 pound) to 18.9 kilograms as eating of chicken meat
on average climbed 0.4 kilogram to 11.8 kilograms, according to
the ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rudy Ruitenberg in Paris at 
